urlhtml: National Conservatory of Arts and Sciences library (eng)
title: National Conservatory of Arts and Sciences library (eng)
description:
The "Conservatoire National des Arts et Métiers (CNAM)" not only is one of the most famous schools in France, housing one of the more interesting museums in Paris, it even has offered a setting for Umberto Eco's novel, "Foucault's Pendulum"... before there was "The Da Vinci Code" and the Louvre's pyramids, there was the CNAM and its pendulum... 

The CNAM Bibliothèque contains 140,000 volumes including 7000 pre-19th c., CNAM archives to 1830, and 3500 periodicals titles including 700 current. 

http://www.cnam.fr/bibliotheque/ 
http://www.cnam.fr 
http://cnum.cnam.fr/ (digital library -- "Conservatoire numérique des Arts & Métiers") 
Email: bibliotheque@cnam.fr

Adresse: 292 rue Saint-Martin, 75141 Paris cedex 03 
t. (CNAM bibliothèque) (0)1.40.27.27.03, t. (CNAM) (0)1.40.27.20.00

title: Bibliothèque Publique d'Information (BPI)
description:
The extraordinary BPI "library as event" constructed in the heart of Paris, near the old Halles Centrales, part of the 1970s Piano & Rogers architectural tour de force which on its opening instantly became one of the great urban gathering-places of this city famous for same: called affectionately "our little oil refinery", the massive & multi-colored steel framing, and pipes and vents, have won the grudging respect even of Paris taxi drivers. The BPI is central Paris' largest truly-public library, crowded with multimedia and hordes of students, and open to all, offering large & popular collections

* BPI main website,
http://www.bpi.fr
* BPI via Minitel: 3615BPI
* Additional information in English at, 
http://www.fyifrance.com/fyi1pli3.htm#BPI
